IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On January 24, 2023, at approximately 0715 hours, members of the Metropolitan Area Drug Task Force and I were conducting proactive drug trafficking interdiction efforts at the Federal Express Facility located at Cargo Bldg. E, BWI Airport, Linthicum, Anne Arundel County, Maryland 21240. During these efforts, I observed a brown cardboard box that displayed numerous shipping anomalies, and it was removed from the delivery stream for further investigation. The shipment displayed the following information (written below as shown on the label): Federal Express tracking number: 3937 2836 3217 this is a unique tracking number assigned only to this parcel. FROM: (626) 557-8246 LUCY PETS SUPPLY LUCY PET SUPPLY 820 E VALLEY BLVD ALHAMBRA CA 91801 UNITED STATES US TO: ANDY SPENCER 14960 BELLE AMI DR LAUREL MD 20707 I noted that the shipment was in a brown box with all the seams taped with clear tape. Further, by querying the Federal Express tracking number: 3937 2836 3217, I discovered that the parcel was sent from Alhambra California a city and state known to this Detective to be a possible source for controlled dangerous substances. Based on the totality of the circumstances, investigators requested that Sergeant Murphy #2936 of the Maryland State Police / Metropolitan Area Drug Task Force along with his canine partner Mia #3191conduct a canine drug scan on the aforementioned parcel identified above bearing Waybill Number 3937 2836 3217 Sergeant Murphy and his canine partner Mia conducted a drug scan on this target parcel at 0818 hours. Sergeant Murphys canine partner Mia displayed several behavioral changes for this targeted parcel bearing tracking number 3937 2836 3217 for the odor of controlled dangerous substances. Sergeant Murphy advised me that canine Mias behavioral changes constitute an alert for the odor of controlled dangerous substances. I authored a search and seizure warrant that was signed and granted by the Honorable Judge E. Nyce of the Prince Georges County District Court of Maryland at 0851 hours. Upon executing the warrant 4,190 grams of marijuana, with a street value of $41,900 was discovered inside the box. A delivery was not attempted due to FEDEX Security entering it as seized by Police. The marijuana was subsequently processed and placed on PH-310497 for destruction. The address was flagged for investigative means and any future shipments to that address. ALL EVENTS OCCURRED IN ANNE ARUNDEL AND PRINCE GEORGES COUNTY MARYLAND
